{"履修期": "春学期前半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course aims to provide students with a foundation in management. It includes discussions on the functions of management, managerial roles, skills, and ethics; traditional and contemporary management issues and challenges; scientific management; the principles of management enunciated by Henri Fayol; the Japanese management system; planning and decision-making; organizational; leadership; motivation; and control. Through these topics, students will enhance their conceptual and analytical power to become future leaders.", "到達目標": "Upon successful completion of\nthe course, students will develop a deeper understanding of the fundamental\nconcepts and principles of management and compare the features of Japanese\nmanagement with those of the Anglo-Saxon style. Also, they will understand management functions, the planning process, how to execute a plan, control deviations\nin planning, and motivate employees through effective leadership. &nbsp;", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Economics, Accounting, and Introduction to Business</span></span></span></span>", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "Face-to-face classes. The class plan is listed at the beginning of each class", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">【Startup Week】Online class (</span></span></span></span>On-demand format) /《90minutes》<div><span lang=\"NL\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"ve